    <stitle>ALTERNATOR: DELCO-REMY 20-SI SERIES, TYPE 300 (BRUSHLESS) - REPAIR PROCEDURES</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>REPAIR PROCEDURES</title>
        <svcsubsecinfo>
            <para>To perform electrical checks of components, remove screws and end plate. Component parts and
                connections are shown in
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0801306">Figure 6</hotlnk>.
            </para>
            <figure id="f0801306" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0801306" filename="../figg08/G0801306.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Rectifier End Frame (Cover Plate Removed)</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. RELAY TERMINAL CONNECTOR</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. CAPACITOR LEAD</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. OUTPUT TERMINAL CONNECTOR</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. CAPACITOR</callout1>
                    <callout1>5. OUTPUT ("POS") TERMINAL:</callout1>
                    <callout1>A. NUT</callout1>
                    <callout1>B. LOCK WASHER</callout1>
                    <callout1>C. WASHER</callout1>
                    <callout1>D. NUT</callout1>
                    <callout1>E. LOCK WASHER</callout1>
                    <callout1>F. WASHER</callout1>
                    <callout1>G. INSULATED WASHER</callout1>
                    <callout1>6. RELAY ("R") TERMINAL:</callout1>
                    <callout1>H. BUSHING</callout1>
                    <callout1>I. WASHER</callout1>
                    <callout1>J. BUSHING</callout1>
                    <callout1>K. WASHER</callout1>
                    <callout1>L. CONNECTOR</callout1>
                    <callout1>M. WASHER</callout1>
                    <callout1>N. NUT</callout1>
                    <callout1>7. FIELD LEADS (2) INSULATED SCREWS (2)</callout1>
                    <callout1>8. REGULATOR</callout1>
                    <callout1>9. DIODE TRIO</callout1>
                    <callout1>10. CONNECTOR</callout1>
                    <callout1>11. RECTIFIER BRIDGE</callout1>
                    <callout1>12. STATOR LEADS</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </svcsubsecinfo>
